SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 178
BY SENATOR MIZELL
HEALTH DEPARTMENT. Requests the Louisiana Department of Health to study and make
recommendations regarding modernization of the state's problem gambling prevention and
education efforts.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana Department of Health to study and make
3 recommendations regarding modernization of the state's problem gambling
4 prevention and education efforts, particularly among youth and young adults, and to
5 examine opportunities for school-based education, higher education engagement,
6 digital support resources, and early intervention strategies.
7 WHEREAS, legalized sports wagering and other forms of gambling have expanded
8 significantly in recent years across Louisiana and the United States; and
9 WHEREAS, young people and young adults are increasingly exposed to
10 gambling-related content through sports, online gaming, social media, advertising, and
11 mobile applications; and
12 WHEREAS, problem gambling may negatively impact mental health, financial
13 well-being, academic performance, family stability, and workforce participation; and
14 WHEREAS, many individuals experiencing gambling-related harm do not seek
15 formal treatment or support until significant personal or financial consequences have
16 occurred; and
17 WHEREAS, prevention and early education efforts may help improve awareness of
18 gambling-related risks and encourage healthier decision-making among youth and young
